[tata:] After that, [mAdhava:] Krishna [cha] and [pAMDava:] Arjuna [pradadhmatu:] sounded [divyau shankhau] their divine conches, [sthitau] standing [mahati syandanE] in their famous chariot [yuktE shwEtai:
hayai:] pulled by white horses.

]

[kr'ShNa] Krishna, [adharmAbhibhAvat] when immorality prevails, [kulastriya:
praduShyanti] the ladies of the clan would be abused.

]

[sankarO] This mixture [narakAyaiva kulaghnAnAm
kulasya cha] leads the clan and its slayers to hell.

