[nAbhinandati]
A person is neither driven by likes [na dvEShTi] nor by dislikes [ya:] when he is [anabhisnEha:] without attachment [sarvatra] in all respects, [prApya] even on obtaining [tattat shubhAshubham] things that he likes or dislikes.

